<SUMMARY>
<!-- PJG ITAG l=10 g=1 f=2 -->
SUMMARY:
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=10 g=1 f=1 -->
 We are amending the Federal Seed Act regulations to remove the origin staining requirements for seed of alfalfa and
red clover grown in Mexico and imported into the United States. The removal of the requirements is necessary to make
the regulations conform to the amendment of the Federal Seed Act by the North American Free Trade Agreement Implementation
Act. The effect of this action is to relieve a restriction on importation of alfalfa and red clover seed from Mexico.

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 02 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
</SUMMARY>
