<!-- PJG ITAG l=28 g=1 f=1 -->
The criteria for determining which countries may be listed in this part as countries from which honeybees or honeybee
semen may be imported into the United States are set forth in 7 U.S.C. 282. In this regard, 7 U.S.C. provides in relevant
part, that:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) In order to prevent the introduction and spread of diseases and parasites harmful to honeybees, and the introduction
of genetically undesirable germ plasm of honeybees, the importation into the United States of all honeybees is prohibited,
except that honeybees may be imported into the United States_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) By the United States Department of Agriculture for experimental or scientific purposes;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) From countries determined by the Secretary of Agriculture_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) To be free of diseases or parasites harmful to honeybees, and undesirable species or subspecies of honeybees;
and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) To have in operation precautions adequate to prevent the importation of honeybees from other countries where
harmful diseases or parasites, or undesirable species or subspecies, of honeybees exist; or
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) From Canada or Mexico, subject to such terms and conditions as the Secretary of Agriculture determines appropriate,
if the Secretary determines that the region of Canada or Mexico from which the honeybees originated is, and is likely
to remain, free of diseases or parasites harmful to honeybees, and undesirable species or subspecies of honeybees.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Honeybee semen may be imported into the United States only from:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Countries determines by the Secretary of Agriculture to be free of undesirable species or subspecies of honeybees,
and which have in operation precautions adequate to prevent the importation of such undesirable honeybees and their
semen; or
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Canada or Mexico, if the Secretary of Agriculture determines that the region of Canada or Mexico from which the
imports originate is, and is likely to remain, free of undesirable species or subspecies of honeybees.
