<SUMMARY>
<!-- PJG ITAG l=10 g=1 f=2 -->
SUMMARY:
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=10 g=1 f=1 -->
 This rule amends certain personnel requirements for cytotechnologists that perform testing in laboratories subject
to the requirements of the Clinical Laboratory Improvement Amendments of 1988 (CLIA). We are providing an adequate
period of time for individuals to gain the necessary 2 years experience performing cytology testing which is currently
included in two of the provisions for qualifying as a cytotechnologist. Also, we are extending the time for individuals
to either meet the educational qualifications by virtue of completing training in an approved cytotechnology training
program or be certified by an approved organization. We are making these changes to prevent the loss of qualified personnel
in the field of cytotechnology.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

