weighs four pounds or more in the round, three and one-half pounds or more dressed with the head on, or three pounds or
more dressed with the head off. Total length means the shortest distance between the tip of the jaw or snout, whichever
extends farthest while the mouth is closed, and the tip of the longest lobe of the tail, measured while the halibut is
lying flat in natural repose, without resort to any force other than the swinging or fanning of the tail.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
