<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940106-0-00093 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940106-0-00021 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4700 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
This section provides a context for the attestation process, to facilitate understanding by health care facilities
that may seek nonimmigrant nurses under H&hyph;1A visas.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Federal agencies' responsibilities.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The United States Department of Labor (DOL), Department of Justice, and Department of State are involved in the H&hyph;1A
visa process. Within DOL, the Employment and Training Administration (ETA) and the Employment Standards Administration
(ESA) have responsibility for different aspects of the process.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Health care facility's attestation responsibilities.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Each health care facility seeking one or more H&hyph;1A nurses shall, as the first step, submit an attestation on 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Form ETA 9029
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
, as described in &sect;
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=7 f=2 -->
XXX
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
.310 of this part, to the designated regional office of the Employment and Training Administration (ETA) of DOL. If
the attestation is found to meet the requirements set at &sect;
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=7 f=2 -->
XXX
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
.310 (a) through (k) of this part, ETA shall accept the attestation for filing, shall return the cover form of the accepted
attestation to the health care facility, and shall notify the Immigration and Naturalization Service (INS) of the
Department of Justice of the filing. As discussed in &sect;
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=7 f=2 -->
XXX
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
.310 of this part, if the facility proposes to utilize alternative methods to comply with Attestation Elements I and/or
IV, or asserts that taking a second timely and significant step under Element IV would be unreasonable, or claims a
bona fide medical emergency exemption from Element IV as a worksite using one or more H&hyph;1A nurses through a nursing
contractor only, additional supporting information and ETA review shall be required.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Visa petitions.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Upon ETA's acceptance of the filing, the health care facility may then file with INS H&hyph;1A visa petitions for the
admission of H&hyph;1A nurses, or to extend the stay of alien nurses currently working at the facility. the facility
shall attach a copy of the accepted attestation form (Form ETA 9029) to the visa petition filed with INS. At the same
time that the facility files a visa petition with INS, it shall also send a copy of the visa petition with INS, it shall
also send a copy of the visa petition to the Chief, Division of Foreign Labor Certifications, U.S. Employment Service,
Employment and Training Administration, Department of Labor, 200 Constitution Avenue, NW., room N&hyph;4456,
Washington, DC 20210.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Visa issuance.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 INS assures that the nonimmigrants possess the required qualifications and credentials to be employed as nurses.
See 8 U.S.C. 1182(m)(1)). The Department of State is responsible for issuing the visa.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Board of Alien Labor Certification Appeals (BALCA) review of attestations accepted and not accepted for filing.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The decision whether or not to accept for filing an attestation which ETA has reviewed, that is: an attestation where
the facility is attesting to alternative methods of compliance with Element I and/or Element IV; an attestation where
the facility is claiming that taking a second timely and significant step would not be reasonable; and/or an attestation
where a facility that is not an employer of H&hyph;1A nurses is claiming a bond fide medical emergency as the basis for
requesting a waiver of Element IV; may be appealed by any interested party to the BALCA.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Complaints.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Complaints concerning misrepresentation in the attestation or failure of the health care facility to carry out the
terms of the attestation may be filed with the Wage and Hour Division (Division), Employment Standards Administration
(ESA) of DOL, according to the procedures set forth in subpart E of this part. Complaints of ``misrepresentation''
may include assertions that a facility's attestations of compliance failed to meet the regulatory standards for
attestation elements under which the attestation was accepted by ETA for filing without ETA review. The Division
shall then investigate, and, where appropriate, after an opportunity for a hearing, assess sanctions and penalties.
Subpart E of this part also provides that interested parties may obtain an administrative law judge hearing and may
seek the Secretary's review of the administrative law judge's decision.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940106-0-00094 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940106-0-00021 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4700 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=7 f=2 -->
XXX
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
.302
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Definitions.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
For the purposes of subparts D and E of this part:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Accepted for filing
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means that the attestation and supporting documentation submitted by the health care facility have been received
by the Employment and Training Administration of the Department of Labor (DOL) and have been found to be in compliance
with the attestation requirements in &sect;
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=7 f=2 -->
XX
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
.310 of this part.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Act
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 and 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
INA
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 mean the Immigration and Nationality Act, as amended, 8 U.S.C. 1101 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
et seq.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Administrative law judge
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means an official appointed pursuant to 5 U.S.C. 3105.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Administrator
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the Administrator of the Wage and Hour Division, Employment Standards Administration, Department of Labor,
and such authorized representatives as may be designated to perform any of the functions of the Administrator under
subparts D and E of this part.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Attorney General
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the chief official of the U.S. Department of Justice or the Attorney General's designee.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Board of Alien Labor Certification Appeals (BALCA)
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means a panel of one or more administrative law judges who serve on the permanent Board of Alien Labor Certification
Appeals established by 20 CFR Part 656. BALCA consists of administrative law judges assigned to the Department of
Labor and designated by the Chief Administrative Law Judge to be members of the Board of Alien Labor Certification
Appeals.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Bona fide medical emergency
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means a situation in which the services of one or more H&hyph;1A contract nurses are necessary at a worksite facility
(which itself does not employ an H&hyph;1A nurse) to prevent death or serious impairment of health, and, because of
the danger to life or health, nursing services for such situation are not elsewhere available in the geographic area.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Certifying Officer
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means a Department of Labor official, or such official's designee, who makes determinations about whether or not
H&hyph;1A attestations are acceptable for filing.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Chief Administrative Law Judge
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the chief official of the Office of the Administrative Law Judges of the Department of Labor or the Chief Administrative
Law Judge's designee.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Chief, Division of Foreign Labor Certifications, USES
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the chief official of the Division of Foreign Labor Certifications within the United States Employment Service,
Employment and Training Administration, Department of Labor, or the designee of the Chief, Division of Foreign Labor
Certifications, USES.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Date of filing
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the date an attestation is ``accepted for filing'' by ETA.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940106-0-00095 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940106-0-00021 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4700 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Department
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 and 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
DOL
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 mean the United States Department of Labor.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Director
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the chief official of the United States Employment Service (USES), Employment and Training Administration,
Department of Labor, or the Director's designee.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Division
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the Wage and Hour Division of the Employment Standards Administration, DOL.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Employer
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means a person, firm, corporation, or other association or organization involved in the direct provision of health
care services, which:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Suffers or permits a person to work;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Has a location within the United States to which U.S. workers may be referred for employment;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Proposes to employ workers at a place within the United States; and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Has an employer-employee relationship with respect to employees under subpart D and E of this part, as indicated
by the fact that it may hire, pay, fire, supervise or otherwise control the work of such employee.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Employment
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means full-time work by an employee for an employer/health care facility other than oneself. ``Full-time work''
means work where the nurse is regularly scheduled to work 40 hours or more per week, unless the facility documents as
part of its attestation that it is common practice for the occupation at the facility or for the occupation in the geographic
area for nurses to work fewer hours per week.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Employment and Training Administration (ETA)
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the agency within the Department of Labor (DOL) which includes the United States Employment Service (USES).
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Employment Standards Administration (ESA)
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the agency within the Department of Labor (DOL) which includes the Wage and Hour Division.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Facility
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means a user of nursing services with either a single site or a group of contiguous locations at which it provides health
care services. ``Facility'' includes an employer of registered nurses which provides health care services in a home
or other setting, such as a hospital, nursing home, or other site of employment, not owned or operated by the employer
(
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
e.g.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
, a visiting nurse association or a nursing contractor). ``Facility'' also includes a private household which employs
or seeks to employ one or more H&hyph;1A nurses, but does not include a private household which uses H&hyph;1A nurses
only through a nursing contractor. Groups of structures which form a campus or separate buildings across the street
from one another are a single facility. However, separate buildings or areas which are not physically connected or
in immediate proximity are a single health care facility if they are in reasonable geographic proximity, used for
the same purpose, and share the same nursing staff and equipment. An example is an entity which manages a nursing home
and a hospital in the same area and which regularly shifts or rotates the nurses between the two. Non-contiguous sites,
even within the same geographic area, which do not share the same nursing staff and operational purposes are not a single
facility. For example, hospitals which are located on opposite sides of a municipality, but which are managed or owned
by a single entity, are separate facilities if they do not regularly share nursing staff and operational purpose.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Geographic area
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the area within normal commuting distance of the place (address) of the intended worksite. If the geographic
area does not include a sufficient number of facilities to make a prevailing wage determination, the term ``geographic
area'' shall be expanded (by the State employment service, unless directed not to do so by the Director) with respect
to the attesting facility to include a sufficient number of facilities to permit a prevailing wage determination
to be made. If the place of the intended worksite is within a Metropolitan Statistical Area (MSA), any place within
the MSA may be deemed to be within normal commuting distance of the place of intended employment.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Governor
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the chief elected official of a State or the Governor's designee.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
H&hyph;1A nurse
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means any nonimmigrant alien admitted to the United States to perform services as a nurse under section 101(a)(15)(H)(i)(a)
of the Act (8 U.S.C. 1101(a)(15)(H)(i)(a)).
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Immigration and Naturalization Service (INS)
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the component of the Department of Justice which makes the determination under the Act on whether to grant visa
petitions to petitioners seeking the admission of nonimmigrant nurses under H&hyph;1A visas.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Layoff
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means any involuntary separation of one or more staff nurses without cause/prejudice. If a staff nurse is separated
from one specialized activity and is offered retraining and retention at the same facility in another activity involving
direct patient care at the same wage and status, but refuses such training and retention, such separation shall not
constitute a layoff. The layoff provision applies to staff nurses only, not to other health occupations. If the position
occupied by the staff nurse is covered by a collective bargaining agreement, the collective bargaining agreement
definition of ``layoff'' (if any) shall apply to that position.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Lockout
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means a labor dispute involving a work stoppage, wherein an employer withholds work from its employees in order to
gain a concession from them.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Nurse
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means a person who is or will be authorized by a State Board of Nursing to engage in registered nursing practice in a State
or U.S. territory or possession at a facility which provides health care services. A staff nurse means a nurse who provides
nursing care directly to patients. In order to qualify under this definition of ``nurse'' the alien shall:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Have obtained a full and unrestricted license to practice nursing in the country where the alien obtained nursing
education, or have received nursing education in the United States or Canada;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Have passed the examination given by the Commission on Graduates for Foreign Nursing Schools (CGFNS), or have
obtained a full and unrestricted (permanent) license to practice as a registered nurse in the state of intended employment,
or have obtained a full and unrestricted (permanent) license in any state or territory of the United States and received
temporary authorization to practice as a registered nurse in the state of intended employment; and,
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Be fully qualified and eligible under the laws (including such temporary or interim licensing requirements which
authorize the nurse to be employed) governing the place of intended employment to practice as a registered nurse immediately
upon admission to the United States, and be authorized under such laws to be employed by the employer. For purposes
of this paragraph, the temporary or interim licensing may be obtained immediately after the alien enters the United
States and registers to take the first available examination for permanent licensure.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940106-0-00096 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940106-0-00021 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4700 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Nursing contractor
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means an entity that employs registered nurses and supplies these nurses, on a temporary basis and for a fee, to health
care facilities or private homes.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Prevailing wage
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the average wage paid to similarly employed registered nurses within the geographic area.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Secretary
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the Secretary of Labor or the Secretary's designee.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Similarly employed
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means employed by the same type of facility (acute care or long-term care) and working under like conditions, such
as the same shift, on the same days of the week, and in the same specialty area.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
State
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means one of the 50 States, the District of Columbia, Puerto Rico, the U.S. Virgin Islands, and Guam.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
State employment security agency (SESA)
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the State agency designated under section 4 of the Wagner-Peyser Act to cooperate with USES in the operation
of the national system of public employment offices.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Strike
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means a labor dispute wherein employees engage in a concerted stoppage or work (including stoppage by reason of the
expiration of a collective-bargaining agreement) or engage in any concerted slowdown or other concerted interruption
of operations.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
United States Employment Service (USES)
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the agency of the Department of Labor, established under the Wagner-Peyser Act, which is charged with administering
the national system of public employment offices.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
United States (U.S.) nurse
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means any nurse who is a U.S. citizen; is a U.S. national; is lawfully admitted for permanent residence; is granted
the status of an alien admitted for temporary residence under 8 U.S.C. 1160(a), 1161(a), or 1255a(a)(1); is admitted
as a refugee under 8 U.S.C. 1157; or is granted asylum under 8 U.S.C. 1158.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
United States (U.S.) worker
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means any worker who is a U.S. citizen; is a U.S. national; is lawfully admitted for permanent residence; is granted
