(B) The employment of the aliens will not adversely affect the wages and working conditions of registered nurses similarly
employed.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(C) The aliens employed by the facility will be paid the wage rate for registered nurses similarly employed by the facility.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(D) Either_(
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
1
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
) The facility has taken and is taking timely and significant steps designed to recruit and retain sufficient registered
nurses who are United States citizens or immigrants who are authorized to perform nursing services, in order to remove
