<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(C) Impact, certification, and expiration dates in the certification document. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(D) Benefits and reemployment services available to eligible workers. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(E) Explanation of how workers apply for TAA benefits and services. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(F) Whom to call to get additional information on the certification. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(G) When and where the workers should come to apply for benefits and services. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Newspaper notices. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(i) Upon receipt of a copy of a certification issued by the Department affecting workers in a State, the State agency
shall publish a notice of such certification in a newspaper of general circulation in areas in which such workers reside.
Such a newspaper notice shall not be required to be published, however, in the case of a certification with respect
to which the State agency can substantiate, and enters in its records evidence substantiating, that all workers covered
by the certification have received written notice required by paragraph (d)(1) of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) A published notice must include the following kinds of information: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) Worker group(s) covered by the certification, and the article(s) produced as specified in the copy of the certification
furnished to the State agency. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) Name and the address or location of workers' firm. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(C) Impact, certification, and expiration dates in the certification document. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(D) Benefits and reemployment services available to eligible workers. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
