<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) Before the expiration of the two-year period beginning on the date of such certification, or, if earlier, before
the termination date, if any, of such certification. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Wages and employment. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(A) In the 52-week period (i.e., 52 consecutive calendar weeks) ending with the week of the individual's first qualifying
separation, or any subsequent total qualifying separation under the same certification, the individual must have
had at least 26 weeks of employment at wages of $30 or more a week in adversely affected employment with a single firm
or subdivision of a firm. Evidence that an individual meets this requirement shall be obtained as provided in &sect;617.12.
Employment and wages covered under more than one certification may not be combined to qualify for TRA. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B)(
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
1
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
) For the purposes of paragraph (a)(2)(iii) of this section, any week in which such individual_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
i
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
) Is on employer-authorized leave from such adversely affected employment for purposes of vacation, sickness, injury,
maternity, or inactive duty or active duty military service for training, or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
ii
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
