the individual is ineligible or subject to disqualification under the applicable State law or &sect;617.18 (b)(2).

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
On and after November 21, 1988. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The conditions stated in paragraphs (a)(2) and (a)(3) of this section shall not be applicable to an individual who
is enrolled in or participating in a training program approved under &sect;617.22 (a), or during a break in the training
program if (as determined for the purposes of &sect;617.15(d)) the individual participated in the training immediately
before the beginning of the break and resumes participation in the training immediately after the break ends. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
12. Paragraph (b) of &sect;617.18 is revised to read as follows: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;617.18 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Disqualifications. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=37 g=1 f=1 -->
* * * * * 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Disqualification of trainees
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
_(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
State law inapplicable. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
A State law shall not be applied to disqualify an individual from receiving either UI or TRA because the individual:

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Is enrolled in or is participating in a training program approved under &sect;617.22(a); or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Refuses work to which the individual has been referred by the State agency, if such work would require the individual
to discontinue training, or if added to hours of training would occupy the individual more than 8 hours a day or 40 hours
a week, except that paragraph (b)(1)(ii) of this section shall not apply to an individual who is ineligible under paragraph
(b)(2) of this section; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Quits work, if the individual was employed in work which was not suitable (as defined in &sect;617.22(a)(1)),
and it was reasonable and necessary for the individual to quit work to begin or continue training approved for the individual
under &sect;617.22(a). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Trainees ineligible. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(i) An individual who, without justifiable cause, fails to begin participation in a training program which is approved
under &sect;617.22(a), or ceases to participate in such training, or for whom a waiver is revoked pursuant to &sect;617.19(c),
shall not be eligible for basic TRA, or any other payment under this part 617, for the week in which such failure, cessation,
or revocation occurred, or any succeeding week thereafter until the week in which the individual begins or resumes
participation in a training program that is approved under &sect;617.22(a). 
