<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(ii) For purposes of this section and other provisions of this Part 617, the following definitions shall be used: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Failed to begin participation. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
A worker shall be determined to have failed to begin participation in a training program when the worker fails to attend
all scheduled training classes and other training activities in the first week of the training program, without justifiable
cause. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Ceased participation. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
A worker shall be determined to have ceased participation in a training program when the worker fails to attend all
scheduled training classes and other training activities scheduled by the training institution in any week of the
training program, without justifiable cause. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(C) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Justifiable cause. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
For the purposes of paragraph (b)(2) of this section, the term ``justifiable cause'' means such reasons as would justify
an individual's conduct when measured by conduct expected of a reasonable individual in like circumstances, including
but not limited to reasons beyond the individual's control and reasons related to the individual's capability to
participate in or complete an approved training program. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=37 g=1 f=1 -->
