13. A new &sect;617.19 is added to read as follows: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;617.19 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Requirement for participation in training. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
In general_
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Basic requirement. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(i) All individuals otherwise entitled to basic TRA, for all weeks beginning on and after November 21, 1988, must either
be enrolled in or participating in a training program approved under &sect;617.22(a), or have completed a training
program approved under &sect;617.22(a), as provided in &sect;617.11(a)(2)(vii), in order to be entitled to basic
TRA payments for any such week (except for continuation of payments during scheduled breaks in training of 14 days
or less under the conditions stated in &sect;617.15(d)). The training requirement of paragraph (a)(1)(i) of this
section shall be waived in writing on an individual basis, solely in regard to entitlement to basic TRA, if approval
of training for the individual is not feasible or is not appropriate, as determined in accordance with paragraph (a)(2)
of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) As a principal condition of entitlement to additional TRA payments, all individuals must actually be participating
in a training program approved under &sect;617.22(a), for all weeks beginning before November 21, 1988, and for all
weeks beginning on and after November 21, 1988 (except for continuation of payments during breaks in training under
the conditions stated in &sect;617.15(d)). Paragraph (a)(2) of this section is not applicable in regard to additional
TRA, and the participation in training requirement of paragraph (a)(1)(ii) of this section may not be waived under
any circumstances. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Waiver of participation requirement. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
When it is determined, in accordance with paragraph (a)(2) of this section, that it is not feasible or is not appropriate
(as such terms are defined in paragraph (b) of this section) to approve a training program for an individual otherwise
entitled to basic TRA, the individual shall be furnished a formal written notice of waiver, with an explanation of
the reason(s) for the waiver and a statement of why training is not feasible or is not appropriate in the case of such
individual. At a minimum, the written statement furnished to the individual shall contain information required
by &sect;617.50(e) as well as the following information: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Name and social security number of the individual; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Petition number under which the worker was certified; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) A statement why the agency has determined that it is not feasible or is not appropriate to approve training for
the individual at that time, and the reason(s) for the finding; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) A statement that the waiver will be revoked at any time that feasible and appropriate training becomes available;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v) Any other advice or information the State agency deems appropriate in informing the individual; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vi) Signature block (with signature) for the appropriate State official; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vii) Signature block (with signature) for the worker's acknowledgement of receipt. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Denial of a waiver. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
In any case in which a determination is made to deny to any individual a waiver of the participation requirement, the
individual shall be furnished a formal written notice of denial of waiver, which shall contain all of the information
required of formal written notices under paragraph (a)(2) of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
