26. Paragraphs (a) and (d) of &sect;617.50 are revised to read as follows: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;617.50 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Determinations of entitlement; notices to individuals. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Determinations of initial applications for TRA or other TAA.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The State Agency whose State law is the applicable State law under &sect;617.16 shall upon the filing of an initial
application for TRA or other TAA promptly determine the individual's entitlement to such TRA or other TAA under this
part 617, and may accept for such purposes information and findings supplied by another State agency under this part
617. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=37 g=1 f=1 -->
* * * * * 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(d) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Use of State law.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 In making determinations or redeterminations under this section, or in reviewing such determinations or redeterminations
under &sect;617.51, a State agency shall apply the regulations in this part 617. As to matters committed by this part
617 to the applicable State law, a State agency, a hearing officer, or a State court shall apply the applicable State
