<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4700 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Training, job search and relocation allowances. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) If an individual fails, with good cause, to complete training, a job search, or a relocation, any payment or portion
of a payment made under this part 617 to such individual or any person that is not properly and necessarily expended
in attempting to complete such training, job search, or relocation, shall constitute an overpayment. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) If an individual fails, without good cause, to complete training, a job search, or a relocation, any payment made
under this part 617 to such individual or any person shall constitute an overpayment. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Such overpayment shall be recovered or waived as provided in paragraph (a) of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Final determination. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Except for overpayments determined by a court of competent jurisdiction, no repayment may be required, and no deduction
may be made, under this section until a determination under paragraph (a) of this section by the State agency has been
made, notice of the determination and an opportunity for a fair hearing thereon has been given to the person or individual
concerned, and the determination has become final. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Deposit. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Any amount recovered by a State agency under this section shall be deposited into the Federal fund or account from which
payment was made. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Procedural requirements. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) The provisions of paragraphs (c), (e), and (g) of &sect;617.50 shall apply to determinations and redeterminations
made pursuant to this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The provisions of &sect;617.51 shall apply to determinations and redeterminations made pursuant to this section.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(g) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Fraud detection and prevention. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
State procedures for the detection and prevention of fraudulent overpayments of TAA shall be, as a minimum, commensurate
with the procedures adopted by the State with respect to State unemployment compensation and consistent with the
Secretary's ``Standard for Fraud and Overpayment Detection,'' Employment Security Manual, Part V, sections 7510&hyph;7515
(Appendix B of this Part). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(h) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Debts due the United States or Others. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) Notwithstanding any provision of this part 617, TAA payable to a person or an individual under this part 617 shall
be applied by the State agency for the recovery by offset of any debt due the United States from the person or individual.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) TAA shall not be applied or used by the State agency in any manner for the payment of any debt of any person or individual
to any State or any other entity or person, except that TRA payable to an individual shall be payable to someone other
than the individual if required by State law and Federal law to satisfy the individual's obligation for child support
or alimony. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Definition of person.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 For purposes of this section, a person includes any employer or other entity or organization as well as the officers
and officials thereof who may bear individual responsibility. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
28. Section 617.59 is amended by adding a new paragraph (h) and a new paragraph (i) to read as follows: 
