<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4700 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=71 g=1 f=1 -->
5004&blank;
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=71 g=1 f=3 -->
Evaluation of Alternative State Provisions
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=21 g=1 f=3 -->
If the State law provisions do not conform to the ``suggested State law requirements'' set forth in sections 5001 and
5002, but the State law contains alternative provisions, the Manpower Administrator, in collaboration with the
State agency, will study the actual or anticipated affect of the alternative provisions. If the Manpower Administrator
concludes that the alternative provisions satisfy the requirements of the Federal law as construed by the Secretary
(see section 5000 B) he will so notify the State agency. If he does not so conclude, he will submit the matter to the Secretary.
